<h2>Why Corporate Websites in Kenya Are Different</h2>
<p>A corporate website carries more weight than a small business site. It needs to communicate professionalism, inspire trust in large clients and partners, and often serve multiple audiences simultaneously, procurement teams, investors, job seekers, and customers.</p>

<p>Getting it right requires a different approach to structure, design, and content.</p>

<h2>What a Corporate Website Needs to Do</h2>
<p>Before designing anything, it's important to define what success looks like. For most Kenyan corporates, the website must:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Establish credibility</strong>, large clients vet suppliers online before making contact</li>
  <li><strong>Communicate scale and capability</strong>, showcasing your team, facilities, and track record</li>
  <li><strong>Generate qualified leads</strong>, B2B enquiries from decision-makers, not just browsers</li>
  <li><strong>Support recruitment</strong>, attract top talent with a compelling careers section</li>
  <li><strong>Rank on Google</strong>, for industry-specific keywords that your buyers search</li>
</ul>

