<h2>Key Sections of a Corporate Website</h2>
<h3>About / Company Story</h3>
<p>A well-written About page builds emotional trust. Include your founding story, mission, and values, but keep it focused on the client, not yourself. Answer the question: <em>"Why should a corporate buyer choose you over your competitors?"</em></p>

<h3>Services or Solutions</h3>
<p>Corporate buyers want specifics. Avoid vague descriptions. Each service page should include: what it is, who it's for, how it's delivered, and proof it works (case studies, testimonials).</p>

<h3>Case Studies & Portfolio</h3>
<p>This is the most important trust signal for B2B buyers. Show real projects with real results. Include the client name (with permission), the challenge, your solution, and measurable outcomes.</p>

<h3>Team Profiles</h3>
<p>Corporate clients want to know who they're dealing with. Professional headshots and brief bios for directors and senior staff significantly increase enquiry rates.</p>

<h3>Certifications & Accreditations</h3>
<p>ISO certifications, industry body memberships, government registration numbers, these should be clearly visible, ideally with logos.</p>

<h2>Design Principles for Corporate Websites</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Principle</th><th>Why It Matters</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Clean, minimal layout</td><td>Signals professionalism; avoids visual clutter that undermines credibility</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Consistent brand colours and fonts</td><td>Builds recognition and trust across all touchpoints</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Fast load speed</td><td>Senior decision-makers won't wait, a slow site loses B2B leads</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Clear CTAs</td><td>Every page should guide the visitor to the next step (enquiry, call, download)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Accessible and WCAG-compliant</td><td>Required for government and large enterprise procurement</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Corporate Website Costs in Kenya</h2>
<p>Corporate website projects in Kenya typically range from <strong>Ksh 80,000 to Ksh 250,000</strong> depending on size and complexity. Factors that affect price:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Number of pages and sections</li>
  <li>Custom illustrations or professional photography</li>
  <li>Multilingual support (English + Swahili)</li>
  <li>Custom integrations (CRM, tender portal, HR system)</li>
  <li>E-commerce or client portal functionality</li>
</ul>

